Implemented the minimal source changes in:

- `serde_derive/src/internals/check.rs`
- `serde_derive/src/ser.rs`

What changed:
- `#[serde(getter = "...")]` is no longer restricted to `#[serde(remote = "...")]` structs.
- Local struct serialization now uses the getter value when serializing the field.
- Unqualified local getter method names like `#[serde(getter = "get_value_with_prefix")]` are supported as method calls on `self`.
- Existing field attributes like `skip_serializing_if`, `serialize_with`, etc. continue to operate on the getter-produced value.

Validation:
- Ran `cargo check -p serde_derive` successfully.
- Also verified a temporary crate compiling a local struct with `#[serde(getter = "...", skip_serializing_if = "...")]`.
